asy]\n\nWhich is the graph of $y = f^{-1}(x)$?\n\n[asy]\nunitsize(0.5 cm);\n\npicture[] graf;\nint i, n;\n\nreal func(real x) {\n  return (log(x));\n}\n\npath foo = graph(func,exp(-5),5); \n\nfor (n = 1; n <= 5; ++n) {\n  graf[n] = new picture;\n  for (i = -5; i <= 5; ++i) {\n    draw(graf[n],(i,-5)--(i,5),gray(0.7));\n    draw(graf[n],(-5,i)--(5,i),gray(0.7));\n  }\n  draw(graf[n],(-5,0)--(5,0),Arrows(6));\n  draw(graf[n],(0,-5)--(0,5),Arrows(6));\n\n  label(graf[n],\"$x$\", (5,0), E);\n  label(graf[n],\"$y$\", (0,5), N);\n}\n\ndraw(graf[1],reflect((0,0),(0,1))*foo,red);\ndraw(graf[2],reflect((0,0),(1,-1))*foo,red);\ndraw(graf[3],reflect((0,0),(1,0))*foo,red);\ndraw(graf[4],rotate(180)*foo,red);\ndraw(graf[5],reflect((0,0),(1,1))*foo,red);\n\nlabel(graf[1], \"A\", (0,-6));\nlabel(graf[2], \"B\", (0,-6));\nlabel(graf[3], \"C\", (0,-6));\nlabel(graf[4], \"D\", (0,-6));\nlabel(graf[5], \"E\", (0,-6));\n\nadd(graf[1]);\nadd(shift((12,0))*(graf[2]));\nadd(shift((24,0))*(graf[3]));\nadd(shift((6,-12))*(graf[4]));\nadd(shift((18,-12))*(graf[5]));\n[/asy]\n\nEnter the letter of the graph of $y = f^{-1}(x).$\nAssistant: <think>", "response": "The graph of $y = f^{-1}(x)$ is the reflection of the graph of $y = f(x)$ across the line $y = x$.</think> <answer>$\\boxed{\\text{A}}$</answer>", "truth": "\\text{E}", "reward_format": 1.0, "reward_answer": 0.0, "reward_total": 0.0}, {"prompt": "A conversation between User and Assistant. The User asks a question, and the Assistant solves it. The Assistant first thinks about the reasoning process in the mind and then provides the User with the answer. The reasoning process is enclosed within <think> </think> and answer is enclosed within <answer> </answer> tags, respectively, i.e., <think> reasoning process here </think> <answer> answer here </answer>.\nUser: Marsha adds all but one of the first ten positive integers. Her sum is a square number. Which one of the first ten positive integers did Marsha not include?\nAssistant: <think>", 